2026 2026
1 23-1717 (1) Except as otherwise provided in subsections (2) and (3)
2 of this section, county County sheriffs and their deputies, when on duty,
3 shall:
4 (a) Be be dressed in a distinctive uniform that is approved by the
5 sheriff and that meets the requirements of , as described in section
6 23-1719; , and
7 (b) Display display a badge of office as described in section
8 23-1719. ;
9 (2) The Provided, the wearing of such uniform and badge shall be
10 discretionary at the option of the sheriff when he or she or his or her
11 deputies are engaged in special investigations or mental patient
12 assignments. ;
13 (3) Special and provided further, that special deputies appointed by
14 the sheriff shall be excluded from the requirements of this section.
15 Sec. 4. Section 23-1719, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
16 amended to read:
17 23-1719 (1) The uniform required by section 23-1717 shall be at the
18 discretion of the sheriff and may be separated into classes to best fit
19 the needs of each sheriff. Any such uniform shall be readily
20 distinguishable from the uniform of other law enforcement agencies in the
21 State of Nebraska.
22 (2) The Class A or dress uniform for a county sheriff or their
23 deputies and shall consist of:
24 (a) Brown felt campaign hat, center crease in sheriff or western
25 style;
26 (b) Brown straw campaign hat, center crease in sheriff or western
27 style;
28 (c) Chocolate brown color shirt with either long or short sleeves
29 depending on season;
30 (d) Pink tan color trousers in appropriate seasonal weights;
31 (e) Pink tan color skirts in appropriate seasonal weights;
-4-

LB784 LB784
2026 2026
1 (e) (f) Pink tan color necktie;
2 (f) (g) Shoes or boots in the same color as the leather worn;
3 (g) (h) Chocolate brown color service jacket, zipper front with
4 badge or insignia approved by the sheriff holder;
5 (h) (i) Hip-length year-round outer jacket, dark brown in color;
6 (i) (j) Badge bearing state or state seal, rank, and county and
7 consisting of a seven-point star; :
8 (i) Gold in color for sheriff and deputies of the rank of sergeant
9 or above;
10 (ii) Silver in color for deputies under the rank of sergeant; and
11 (iii) Consisting of seven-point star;
12 (j) (k) Collar ornaments : (i) Gold for sheriff and deputies; of the
13 rank of sergeant or above; and
14 (ii) Silver for deputies under the rank of sergeant;
15 (k) (l) Shoulder emblem to be worn on upper sleeve and include
16 sheriff's office or department and county name - design optional;
17 (l) (m) Leather to be either brown or black at the individual
18 department's choice; and
19 (m) (n) Brown winter cap with flap.
20 (3) The Class B or patrol uniform for a county sheriff or their
21 deputies shall consist of:
22 (a) Black or any variation of brown hat, depending on the season;
23 (b) Black or any variation of brown color external carrier, with
24 badge;
25 (c) Black or any variation of brown color shirt with either long or
26 short sleeves depending on season;
27 (d) Black or any variation of brown color trousers in appropriate
28 seasonal weights;
29 (e) Black or any variation of brown color shoes or boots;
30 (f) Black or any variation of brown color jacket, with a badge or
31 insignia approved by the sheriff;
-5-

