1 (g) Badge bearing state or state seal, rank, and county and
2 consisting of a seven-point star;
3 (h) Shoulder emblem to be worn on upper sleeve and include sheriff's
4 office or department and county name - design optional; and
5 (i) Leather to be either black or any variation of brown at the
6 individual department's choice.
7 (4) The honor guard or color guard uniform for a county sheriff or
8 their deputies shall consist of:
9 (a) Any variation of brown color campaign hat, center crease in
10 sheriff or western style;
11 (b) Any variation of brown color uniform jacket;
12 (c) Any variation of brown color pants;
13 (d) Black leather shoes or boots;
14 (e) Shoulder emblem to be worn on upper sleeve and include sheriff's
15 office or department and county name - design optional; and
16 (f) Badge bearing state or state seal, rank, and county and
17 consisting of a seven-point star.
18 (2) Uniforms shall be purchased directly from the supplier or
19 suppliers with whom the Department of Administrative Services has
20 contracted.
21 (5) (3) A committee from the Nebraska Sheriffs' and Peace Officers'
22 Association shall assist the Department of Administrative Services in
23 developing specifications and selecting material for the uniforms.
24 Sec. 5. Section 32-604, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
25 2024, is amended to read:
26 32-604 (1) Except as provided in subsection (2) or (4) of this
27 section, no person shall be precluded from being elected or appointed to
28 or holding an elective office for the reason that he or she has been
29 elected or appointed to or holds another elective office.
30 (2) No person serving as a member of the Legislature or in an
31 elective office described in Article IV, section 1 or 20, or Article VII,
-6-

LB784 LB784
2026 2026
1 section 3 or 10, of the Constitution of Nebraska shall simultaneously
2 serve in any other elective office, except that such a person may
3 simultaneously serve in another elective office which is filled at an
4 election held in conjunction with the annual meeting of a public body.
5 (3) Whenever an incumbent serving as a member of the Legislature or
6 in an elective office described in Article IV, section 1 or 20, or
7 Article VII, section 3 or 10, of the Constitution of Nebraska assumes
8 another elective office, except an elective office filled at an election
9 held in conjunction with the annual meeting of a public body, the office
10 first held by the incumbent shall be deemed vacant.
11 (4) No person serving in a high elective office shall simultaneously
12 serve in any other high elective office, except that (a) a county
13 attorney may serve as the county attorney for more than one county if
14 appointed under subsection (2) of section 23-1201.01 and (b) a county
15 sheriff may serve as the county sheriff for more than one county if
16 appointed under subsection (4) (3) of section 23-1701.
17 (5) Notwithstanding subsection (4) of this section, any person
18 holding more than one high elective office upon July 15, 2010, shall be
19 entitled to serve the remainder of all terms for which he or she was
20 elected or appointed.
21 (6) For purposes of this section, (a) elective office has the
22 meaning found in section 32-109 and includes an office which is filled at
23 an election held in conjunction with the annual meeting of a public body
24 created by an act of the Legislature but does not include a member of a
25 learning community coordinating council appointed pursuant to subsection
26 (5) or (7) of section 32-546.01 prior to January 5, 2017, and (b) high
27 elective office means a member of the Legislature, an elective office
28 described in Article IV, section 1 or 20, or Article VII, section 3 or
29 10, of the Constitution of Nebraska, or a county, city, community college
30 area, learning community, regional metropolitan transit authority, or
31 school district elective office.
