1 Sec. 6. Section 81-1414.07, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 81-1414.07 (1)(a) In order to maintain his or her professional
4 status and serve the law enforcement profession, the community, and the
5 residents of Nebraska, each law enforcement officer , other than a
6 noncertified conditional officer, shall attend continuing education
7 courses for the number of hours required in subdivision (1)(b) of this
8 section in the areas of criminal justice and law enforcement as provided
9 in this section. during each calendar year beginning on January 1 and
10 ending on December 31.
11 (b) A law enforcement officer is not required to meet the continuing
12 education requirements in the year in which he or she first becomes fully
13 certified.
14 (c) A law enforcement officer may retire from service in good
15 standing without meeting the continuing education requirements in the
16 calendar year of the officer's retirement.
17 (d) The requirements of this section do not apply to a noncertified
18 conditional officer.
19 (b) The number of continuing education hours required under this
20 subsection shall be:
21 (i) Until January 1, 2022, twenty hours;
22 (ii) Beginning January 1, 2022, and until January 1, 2023, twenty-
23 eight hours; and
24 (iii) Beginning January 1, 2023, thirty-two hours.
25 (2)(a) Each calendar year, a law enforcement officer shall attend at
26 least:
27 (i) For a law enforcement officer employed by a law enforcement
28 agency that employs less than twenty-five full-time law enforcement
29 officers, twenty-four hours of continuing education; and
30 (ii) For a law enforcement officer employed by a law enforcement
31 agency that employs twenty-five or more full-time law enforcement
-8-

LB784 LB784
2026 2026
1 officers, thirty-two hours of continuing education.
2 (b) Such annual continuing education (2) The annual continuing
3 education required by this section shall include:
4 (i) A refresher course on de-escalation;
5 (a) Refresher courses on de-escalation, mental health, and substance
6 abuse issues;
7 (ii) (b) A minimum of two hours of anti-bias and implicit bias
8 training;
9 (iii) (c) Firearms training;
10 (iv) (d) Officer wellness training;
11 (v) (e) Legal update training updates, including, but not limited
12 to, legislative changes and First Amendment and Fourth Amendment issues;
13 and
14 (f) Vehicular pursuit policy review; and
15 (vi) (g) Any other training as determined by a law enforcement
16 agency.
17 (3)(a) At least once in each three-calendar-year period, a law
18 enforcement officer shall attend continuing education that includes:
19 (i) Refresher courses on mental health and substance abuse issues;
20 and
21 (ii) A review of vehicular pursuit policies.
22 (b) The continuing education hours required by this subsection are
23 counted for purposes of the required hours under subsection (2) of this
24 section.
25 (4) (3) Continuing education courses may be offered in the form of
26 seminars, advanced education which may include college or university
27 classes, conferences, instruction conducted within the law enforcement
28 officer's law enforcement agency, or instruction conducted over the
29 Internet. Continuing education shall be of a type which has application
30 to and seeks to maintain and improve the skills of the law enforcement
31 officer in carrying out his or her duties and responsibilities.
